  <h1 id="Welcome">9VoltCat Industries</h1>
  <h2 id="introshort">3D logo animation</h2>
  <p class="margin-400">
         Was itching to try and make fake lightening in blender. 
         Its a lot of fun building up a bolt of lightening, and using the displacement modifier to get that electric jitter. 
         Pairing it with an emission shader, and a rigged lattice made a pretty cool looking bolt of lighting. 
         although it looked a little janky from wireframe view, since I'm switching from transparent to emission on the fly, to get that flash effect. 
         In retrospect, I think I could have gotten away with just shrinking the while lattice rig away. But putting it in the reflection made it look a lot prettier, more ambient. 
         Definitely not my best work but I want to improve it when I get the computer power. This was, as i said before, done in blender.
    </p>
    <p id="credits">Animation - Jordan Cruz<br> 2021 </p>
